                <td style={{ padding: "0.75rem 0.5rem", color: "#666", fontSize: "0.75rem" }}>
                  {product.lastSynced
                    ? new Date(product.lastSynced).toLocaleTimeString()
                    : "—"}
                </td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <details style={{ marginTop: "2rem", fontSize: "0.8rem", color: "#888" }}>
        <summary style={{ cursor: "pointer" }}>How eventual consistency works here</summary>
        <ol style={{ marginTop: "0.5rem", paddingLeft: "1.25rem", lineHeight: 1.8 }}>
          <li>
            <strong>Sync triggered</strong> — the form POSTs to the inline
            Server Action which fires <code>syncCatalog()</code> in the
            background (takes ~4 s).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cache invalidated</strong> —{" "}
            <code>revalidateTag(&quot;products&quot;)</code> marks every
            data-fetch tagged <code>&quot;products&quot;</code> as stale.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Page re-renders</strong> — the product list loads from
            the data layer immediately. If the sync hasn&apos;t finished yet
            the prices / stock are the <em>previous</em> values — briefly
            stale.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Sync completes</strong> — the background job writes
            updated pricing and inventory. Any subsequent page visit or
            re-render (click around, navigate away and back) picks up the
            fresh data because the cache tag is already invalidated.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </details>
    </div>
  );
}

